
Add this TXT record to the send.kibamail.com DNS zone.

aug2024._domainkey    IN   TXT   v=DKIM1;


BIND zone file formatted:

aug2024._domainkey    IN   TXT (
	"v=DKIM1;p=MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEAr3vFC5wGdDjAB6KsMdxIKrfkWaZ0q1A/ZMVO7ta1h6cGEIuYpTAoZC/J"
	"MDyn8fgg2b7nPsPwK/M9qlFeZ21x/VjFuOHretJIek/akgLeYmDd+Vnws4l4gpf59ax3WZsPl3BCNVmLNw+wZgJe3+RUMNyuHA4QEPgd37OEis"
	"v4j93592rmHipIsZUWy9ExP8j5cth9uPt797Y1GBQxsRkEBAPTQWOeIVoiHn2bLNGKS4kniD1BI4JXediJUs5FoJkZ/8bwjc2MpN89onqeqRhw"
	"aHzaazYB4E/wD5vKxq2+u399dN1hVs/DmPTRhSAcBmnVtCsLx9a8Sup+p95Yw/+l4wIDAQAB"
        )

Tell the world that the ONLY mail servers that send mail from this domain are DKIM signed and/or bear our MX and A records.

With SPF:

        SPF "v=spf1 mx a -all"
        TXT "v=spf1 mx a -all"

With DMARC:

_dmarc  TXT "v=DMARC1; p=reject; adkim=s; aspf=r; rua=mailto:dmarc-feedback@send.kibamail.com; ruf=mailto:dmarc-feedback@send.kibamail.com; pct=100"

For more information about DKIM and SPF policy,
the documentation within each plugin contains a longer discussion and links to more detailed information:

   haraka -h dkim_sign
   haraka -h spf

